{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["5678","5680","5683","5684","5687","5688","5691","5692","5693","5708","5709","5711","5714","5717","5720","5724","5728","5729","5730","5731","5734","5735","5737","5738","5739","5740","5741","5743","5754","5759","5762","5764","5766"],"resolution_notes":"I adjusted the score regarding the agent not calling the Main Contact and Site Contacts, as the task note indicates these are the same as the task contact. I verified this on the customer’s account and, since it was documented—including the reason the Google contact was not called (although that decision was not aligned with expectations)—I also updated the question, ‘Was the task notes field completed properly?’ to Yes.

However, the agent was instructed to call (314) 231-7220 x4445 back if she reached the billing contact’s voicemail so that she could be transferred to Accounting. She did not make a callback attempt, and she also chose not to call the Google contact based on her personal assessment that it would not be useful. This is not consistent with the Methods for Making Contact KB page, specifically the ‘Google Research’ scenario - http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/methods-for-making-contact. Following these steps is required for proper contact attempts and documentation.

The original score was 58.27%. The score has been updated.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["5979","5980","5981","5982","5983","5986","5989","5990","5992","5995","5999","6000","6002","6003","6004","6006","6007","6012","6018","6019","6020","6021","6022","6024","6031","6040","6041","6042","6043","6044","6045","6046","6048","6049","6050","6051","6052","6054","6055","6056","6057","6058","6059","6060","6062","6063","6065","6071","6072","6073","6074","6075","6076","6077","6078","6079","6080","6082","6083","6084","6085","6087","6090","6094"],"resolution_notes":"The score was adjusted for the question, ‘Did the agent wait for the customer to hang up first?’ It appears we will need to update the KB to clarify that CSRs should not remain on the line in silence for an extended period if the customer does not disconnect.

For the question, ‘Were appropriate and relevant questions asked?’ the agent did not use the Music Players Supported by Dynamic Media KB page to accurately describe and verify the customer’s device.

For the question, ‘Excluding scripting, did the agent use the Knowledge Base correctly?’ the agent did not escalate the customer’s question as required by the Policy – Asking Questions and Providing Answers KB page. The original score was 92.42%. Score has been updated.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["5769","5771","5774","5778","5782","5783","5784","5785","5799","5802","5805","5808","5811","5815","5819","5820","5821","5822","5825","5826","5828","5829","5830","5831","5832","5834","5845","5850","5853","5855","5857"],"resolution_notes":""I adjusted the score for the question ‘Were any additional numbers found that could be called?’ A Google number was located, contacted, and a voicemail was left, so this item was updated accordingly.

I also adjusted the question ‘At any point during the contact attempt did the agent talk to a person or leave a voicemail/message?’ since the agent did leave a voicemail for the Google contact.

Lastly, I updated ‘Was the task notes field completed properly?’ to Yes, as the notes were documented correctly. The previous comment regarding the Google research can be voided, and the call was verified in the agent’s call log."The original score was 83.72%. Score has been updated.","resolved_by":8}

