{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The score remains unchanged following the review. Although the agent documented that the Google contact was not called due to no information being available, further review shows that this step was not completed in accordance with the KB requirements.

When searching the address alone, no phone number appears; however, per the KB instructions, searching the site name and address together does return a Google contact. The agent did not perform this required search as outlined in the KB page Methods for Making Contact.

As a result, the original score of 89.06% remains, and the score has been updated accordingly.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The score remains unchanged following review. The agent did not Google the site name and address as required by the KB page Methods for Making Contact (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/methods-for-making-contact
).

Additionally, full contact methods and documentation were not completed. The notes do not indicate why the site contact and Google contact were not called, nor do they include the business hours, as required by the KB page How to Document Methods for Making Contact (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-document-methods-for-making-contact
).

As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The score remains unchanged following the review. The agent did not use the required scripting or follow the steps outlined in the KB article How to Process a Change of Ownership (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-process-a-change-of-ownership
).

Additionally, the agent did not follow the required scripting to send an exit survey per the KB article How to Send an Exit Survey (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-send-an-exit-survey
). The agent also did not utilize positive scripting as required by the KB article Positive Scripting – Words and Phrases (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/phone-etiquette-tickets-and-tasks/page/positive-scripting-words-and-phrases
).
As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The score remains unchanged following the review. The agent did not follow the ticket follow-up cadence requirements outlined in the KB page Cadence Guide (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-outbound-bdr/page/cadence-guide
). The interaction required additional follow-up.

Although the agent did place a return call per the notes, only a voicemail was left. The agent did not complete the required ticket follow-up process, which includes sending an email and making at least three follow-up attempts unless the customer responds or the third attempt is completed.

Additionally, the ticket status should have remained open, with the NCD set to the next business day. The resolution should have been set to Unresolved until the CSR was able to successfully speak with or received an email from the customer.

As a result, required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

