{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["6217","6218","6219","6220","6221","6222","6224","6227","6230","6233","6237","6238","6240","6241","6242","6244","6250","6256","6262","6269","6278","6279","6280","6281","6282","6283","6284","6286","6287","6288","6289","6290","6292","6293","6294","6295","6296","6297","6298","6300","6301","6303","6309","6310","6311","6312","6313","6314","6315","6316","6317","6318","6320","6325","6328","6330","6332","6335"],"resolution_notes":"I updated the score for “Was the customer account properly located in the CRM?” to No. The agent did not locate the customer’s account in the CRM. Instead, the agent asked whether the caller was near the player to obtain additional details to assist with locating the account. The caller then provided an alternate number, 734-410-8673, which was confirmed to be the customer’s cell phone number.

The agent immediately placed a call to the cell phone number; however, the customer indicated she was busy and stated she would call back in approximately one hour. The agent did not follow up after the stated time frame to continue the account-location process and initiate support. A follow-up call should have been made once the hour had passed.

I also adjusted “Did the agent determine if this was a new or existing issue/request?” and “Did the agent restate the caller’s need before beginning the support interaction?” to Yes. These were updated to “Yes” at this time due to the absence of an N/A option.

The score for “Excluding scripting, did the agent use the Knowledge Base correctly?” remains No, as the agent did not attempt all required account search methods outlined in the Knowledge Base article How to Search for an Account (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/how-to-search-for-an-account
). Specifically, the agent did not attempt to search using the customer’s email address.

The original score was 60.16%. The score has since been updated to reflect these adjustments.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["6337","6339","6340","6342","6343","6344","6346","6350","6351","6352","6353","6367","6368","6370","6373","6376","6379","6383","6387","6388","6389","6390","6393","6394","6396","6397","6398","6399","6400","6402","6413","6418","6421","6425"],"resolution_notes":"The notes from the 2/24 touch are unclear, making it difficult to determine which phone number belongs to which contact. It appears that 936-598-3311 was the Billing contact and also listed as the Google contact, while (936) 598-1185 was the Customer contact at the time. Because the contacts were updated on the same day and the representative did not clearly document the details, it is not possible to confirm which number was associated with the Site contact at that time.

Currently, (936) 598-1185 is listed as the Billing, Customer, and Site contact, and 936-598-3311 is listed as the Google contact.

After listening to both calls, I adjusted the score related to the correct voicemail script being used. The original score was 90.34%, and the score has now been updated.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["6217","6218","6219","6220","6221","6224","6227","6230","6233","6237","6238","6240","6241","6242","6244","6250","6256","6262","6269","6278","6286","6287","6288","6289","6290","6292","6293","6295","6296","6297","6300","6301","6303","6309","6310","6311","6312","6313","6314","6315","6316","6317","6318","6320","6321","6322","6323","6325","6328","6330","6332","6335"],"resolution_notes":"I adjusted the score for Was the ticket notes field completed properly. Interaction ID 3f985317-c8f1-4091-b07d-2045dbe942b8 was disconnected, and the agent promptly called the customer back under Interaction ID f44669ff-9a44-4aaf-aa9c-65b509bc3608. During that call, it was determined that a return call would be made at 2:30 PM, which was properly documented in the notes.

I also adjusted the score related to the agent’s use of ChatGPT, as the agent followed KB instructions by using Google to locate the amplifier manual and used ChatGPT to identify the correct cable needed to connect the iPad to the amplifier. Based on this interaction, the Knowledge Base should be reviewed to determine if an update is needed to provide clearer guidance on acceptable tools and resources.

The original score was 92.94%. The score has been updated.","resolved_by":8}

