{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The audit score remains unchanged following the review. The invoice was partially paid, with the tax portion remaining outstanding. The Admin noted in the task that the taxes were unpaid and requested that the agent follow up with the customer to confirm whether the account is tax exempt.

Per process, required contact attempts should continue until the invoice is paid in full or clarification is received regarding the outstanding balance. The agent did not complete the Methods for Making Contact in accordance with the requirements outlined in the KB page: http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/methods-for-making-contact.

Additionally, there was no documentation explaining why the required contact methods were not completed. As a result, the required call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The audit score remains unchanged following the review. At the beginning of the call, the agent offered to transfer the customer to their sales representative. However, later in the call, while reviewing information about an alternative channel option for the second time, the agent advised that she would create a ticket and have Sales reach out rather than offering to transfer the call immediately, as required by the KB policy “Offering Alternative Options.”
http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/operations-department-policies/page/policy-offering-alternative-options

The ticket was reassigned to the sales representative, indicating that no additional technical support troubleshooting was intended by the agent. However, because the immediate transfer option was not offered again at that time as required by the policy, the required call process was not fully followed. As a result, the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"REJECTED","updated_answers":[],"resolution_notes":"The audit score remains unchanged following the review. The agent should have documented the troubleshooting notes in the Technical Support ticket (Ticket #274434) rather than the Shipping ticket (Ticket #274838). Additionally, the ticket subclassification should have been updated to reflect the new error message but was not.

Per the requirements outlined in the KB page Ticket Handling – “Do’s and Don’ts” (http://know.crm.dm-us.com/books/job-billing-customer-service/page/ticket-handling-dos-and-donts), under the scenario “Classification / Subclassification,” agents are required to update the ticket classification and subclassification based on the current need within the ticket.

Because the appropriate ticket documentation and classification updates were not completed as required, the call processes were not fully followed, and the audit score remains as originally assessed.","resolved_by":8}

{"status":"ADJUSTED","updated_answers":["6337","6339","6342","6346","6350","6351","6352","6353","6367","6368","6370","6373","6376","6379","6383","6387","6388","6389","6390","6393","6394","6396","6397","6398","6399","6400","6402","6413","6418","6421","6423","6425"],"resolution_notes":"The score has been adjusted regarding the question, “Was the proper script followed when leaving a voicemail/message for the Google contact?” Upon review, the agent did review the account notes, identified the cancellation request, and contacted the customer to confirm the cancellation rather than requesting payment for the open invoice.

However, the agent attempted calls to both 610-258-8110 and 610-252-1212, and there are no corresponding notes documenting these call attempts. The notes field also remains incomplete.

The original score was 77.71%, and the audit score has been updated accordingly","resolved_by":8}

